                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.675,
                                "byte_start": 77439,
                                "byte_stop": 116205,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in 80-1070, Ridgway against Ridgway will be announced by Mr. Justice Blackmun."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.675,
                        "stop": 181.549,
                        "byte_start": 116205,
                        "byte_stop": 803643,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15045,
                            "name": "Harry A. Blackmun",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/harry_a_blackmun",
                            "last_name": "Blackmun",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2689,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 13755600,
                                    "date_end": 775890000,
                                    "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2689"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32712,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 50281,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/harry_a_blackmun.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8821,
                            "identifier": "harry_a_blackmun"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.675,
                                "stop": 34.147,
                                "byte_start": 116205,
                                "byte_stop": 214112,
                                "text": "This case presents the issue whether an insured serviceman\u0027s beneficiary designated under a life policy issued pursuant to the Servicemen\u0027s Group Life Insurance Act of 1965 prevails over a constructive trust imposed upon the policy proceeds by a state-court decree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.147,
                                "stop": 44.484,
                                "byte_start": 214112,
                                "byte_stop": 255385,
                                "text": "It is another in a line of recent cases that concerns the impact of state law or state judgments upon statutorily created federal rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.484,
                                "stop": 48.66,
                                "byte_start": 255385,
                                "byte_stop": 272103,
                                "text": "This is a dispute over the proceeds of a serviceman\u0027s policy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.66,
                                "stop": 61.506,
                                "byte_start": 272103,
                                "byte_stop": 323512,
                                "text": "On the one side of the serviceman\u0027s first wife and their children and on the other, his second wife, who was his widow at his death. Each claimed the policy proceeds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.506,
                                "stop": 66.093,
                                "byte_start": 323512,
                                "byte_stop": 341903,
                                "text": "The former\u0027s claim rested on a divorce decree of a Maine court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.093,
                                "stop": 72.257,
                                "byte_start": 341903,
                                "byte_stop": 366562,
                                "text": "And the widow\u0027s claim rested on the beneficiary designation and her status as widow."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.257,
                                "stop": 83.965,
                                "byte_start": 366562,
                                "byte_stop": 413374,
                                "text": "The trial court felt that the imposition of a constructive trust on the policy proceeds would interfere with the operation of a federal Act and would run afoul of the Supremacy Clause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.965,
                                "stop": 88.869,
                                "byte_start": 413374,
                                "byte_stop": 433018,
                                "text": "The Supreme Judicial Court of Maine ruled otherwise and reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.869,
                                "stop": 96.667,
                                "byte_start": 433018,
                                "byte_stop": 464156,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the clerk today, we in turn reversed the judgment of the Supreme Judicial Court of Maine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.667,
                                "stop": 107.422,
                                "byte_start": 464156,
                                "byte_stop": 507206,
                                "text": "We hold that the insured\u0027s beneficiary designation prevails over the constructive trust imposed upon the policy proceeds by the state court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 107.422,
                                "stop": 121.148,
                                "byte_start": 507206,
                                "byte_stop": 562063,
                                "text": "As a consequence of the Supremacy Clause, a state divorce decree, like other law governing the economic aspects of domestic relations, must give way to clearly conflicting federal enactments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.148,
                                "stop": 130.89,
                                "byte_start": 562063,
                                "byte_stop": 601037,
                                "text": "The provision of the Act according the insured service members certain rights prevail over and displace inconsistent state law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.89,
                                "stop": 139.435,
                                "byte_start": 601037,
                                "byte_stop": 635206,
                                "text": "The imposition of a constructive trust on the insurance proceed is also inconsistent with the anti-attachment provision of the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.435,
                                "stop": 144.344,
                                "byte_start": 635206,
                                "byte_stop": 654850,
                                "text": "A result of this kind, of course, may be avoided if Congress chooses to avoid it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.344,
                                "stop": 146.974,
                                "byte_start": 654850,
                                "byte_stop": 665403,
                                "text": "It is within the power of the Congress."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.974,
                                "stop": 164.565,
                                "byte_start": 665403,
                                "byte_stop": 735725,
                                "text": "But thus far, Congress has insulated the proceeds of this insurance from attachment or seizure by any claimant other than the beneficiary designated by the insured or the one first in line under the statutory order of precedence of beneficiaries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.565,
                                "stop": 172.191,
                                "byte_start": 735725,
                                "byte_stop": 766236,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Powell has filed a dissenting opinion and is joined in that opinion by Mr. Justice Rehnquist."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.191,
                                "stop": 181.549,
                                "byte_start": 766236,
                                "byte_stop": 803643,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Stevens has also filed a dissent and Justice O\u0027Connor took no part in the consideration or decision of this case."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
